-- CIC seeks to raise as much as $318 mln from sale of Noble shares-sheet
-- By Fiona Lau of IFR in HONG KONG
-- Mon Sep 29, 2014 08:44PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Sept 30 (Reuters) - China Investment Corp [CIC.UL] is looking to raise as much as S$405 million ($318 million) by selling about a third of its shares in commodity trader Noble Group Ltd <NOBG.SI>.

CIC, China's sovereign wealth fund, plans to sell 300 million shares in Noble through a wholly-owned subsidiary, priced in the range of S$1.32-S$1.35 per share, a term sheet obtained by IFR showed.  Prior to the sale, CIC holds 930.56 million shares in Noble Group and is its second-largest shareholder, Reuters data showed.